name: UGC_11397
text1: "Its source was the spiral galaxy UGC 11397
text2: which resides in the constellation Lyra (The Lyre)"

name: Horsehead_Nebula
text1: "Hubble Sees a Horsehead of a Different Color"
text2: "Backlit wisps along the Horsehead Nebula upper ridge are being illuminated by Sigma Orionis
text3: a young five-star system just off the top of this image from the Hubble Space Telescope."
